From: electron-rare <c.saillant@gmail.com>
Date: 2026-05-11
Subject: [PATCH] gemma4_text: filter KV-shared k_proj/v_proj/k_norm in sanitize()

Gemma4 architectures with `num_kv_shared_layers > 0` reuse K/V projections
from earlier layers in the later layers. Quantized checkpoints from
`lmstudio-community/gemma-4-*-it-MLX-*bit` (and others) ship the redundant
`k_proj`, `v_proj` and `k_norm` tensors for those KV-shared layers in the
safetensors. Without filtering, `mlx_lm.utils.load_model` raises:

    ValueError: Received parameters not in model: <list...>.

This patch reproduces the same logic as `make_cache` (which already accounts
for `first_kv_shared = num_hidden_layers - num_kv_shared_layers`) inside
`sanitize()`, dropping any K/V projection or K-norm tensor whose layer index
is >= first_kv_shared.

Reproducer
----------

    python -m mlx_lm generate --model lmstudio-community/gemma-4-E4B-it-MLX-4bit \
        --prompt "hello"

    # Without the patch:
    # ValueError: Received 126 parameters not in model: [...]

Tested on
---------
- macOS 26 (M1 Max, 64 GB)
- macOS 26 (M3 Ultra, 512 GB)
- mlx-lm 0.31.3 / mlx 0.29.x

--- a/mlx_lm/models/gemma4_text.py
+++ b/mlx_lm/models/gemma4_text.py
@@ -609,6 +609,7 @@

     def sanitize(self, weights):
         sanitized = {}
+        first_kv_shared = self.args.num_hidden_layers - self.args.num_kv_shared_layers
         for k, v in weights.items():
             if any(
                 s in k
@@ -622,6 +623,18 @@
             ):
                 continue

+            # KV-shared layers reuse K/V from earlier layers — drop their projections
+            if any(
+                s in k
+                for s in (".self_attn.k_proj", ".self_attn.v_proj", ".self_attn.k_norm")
+            ):
+                try:
+                    layer_idx = int(k.split("layers.")[1].split(".")[0])
+                    if layer_idx >= first_kv_shared:
+                        continue
+                except (IndexError, ValueError):
+                    pass
+
             if k.endswith(".experts.gate_up_proj"):
                 base = k.removesuffix(".gate_up_proj")
                 gate, up = map(mx.contiguous, mx.split(v, 2, axis=-2))
